<br>
2 friends an myself group together a lot and we have noticed something most disturbing.<br>
<br>
33 BST (noob gear for the most part cept a soso piercer)<br>
29 DRU (noob gear - mostly acting as healer)<br>
31 MAG (pretty much noob gear)<br>
<br>
AFAIK - the pet taking exp thing was changed so that a SINGLE pet has to outdamage the rest of the party (are other pets counted as part of the rest of the party for this?)<br>
<br>
The problem is - I have the DRU watch his exp bar while medding, if the MAG pet is in the fight from the beginning we all get about 1/2 the exp per kill on a white to me mob (approx number from watching the new blue ticks - not an exact - but it is noticable).<br>
<br>
If we make the mag wait till the mob is at half - we get quite a bit more exp per kill.<br>
<br>
Is the MAG pet really outdamaging us all? I realise we are not the most DPS oriented group - but still......<br>
<br>
Any tips or tricks on keeping the MAG in our group (he is a friend in RL) and not crippling our exp to the point where I might as well go pharm greens for cash?<br>
<br>
Thanks for any help on this!!<br>
<br>
Skorv - the KB newb Beastlord <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uiwanthewicca.showPublicProfile?language=EN>IwanTheWicca</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 75<br> <font color=#333333>(8/3/02 11:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=614.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: A question on grouping for the mage masters :)</span><hr size=1> Pet exp has been drastically changed. SO long as even ONE HP of damage is done by anything other than the pet, then the pet gets ZERO exp!<br>
<br>
